# Multi-Agent Business Intelligence System ‚Äî General Rules

## Project overview
This is a multi-agent AI system that monitors a founder's business (Shopify + Meta/Google Ads + ClickHouse data warehouse) and generates actionable insights. It routes signals through a LangGraph orchestrator to specialist agents, then executes or queues approved actions.

**Core data flow:**
Signal fired (every 15 min) ‚Üí Orchestrator (LangGraph) ‚Üí Agent(s) ‚Üí ActionProposal ‚Üí Guardrail ‚Üí AUTO execute OR Approval queue ‚Üí Outcome store ‚Üí Signal calibration

**Services:**
- `services/orchestrator` ‚Äî Python FastAPI + LangGraph, the central brain
- `services/agents/*` ‚Äî Individual specialist agents (insight, meta, shopify, guardrail)
- `services/worker` ‚Äî BullMQ async job processor (Node.js)
- `services/mcp-shopify` ‚Äî Custom Shopify MCP server (Node.js)
- `apps/web` ‚Äî Next.js 14 App Router frontend
- `packages/db` ‚Äî Prisma schema + migrations
- `packages/shared-types` ‚Äî TypeScript types shared across services

## Naming conventions

### Python (services/orchestrator, services/agents)
- Files: `snake_case.py`
- Classes: `PascalCase`
- Functions/variables: `snake_case`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Pydantic models: suffix with `Schema` for API I/O, no suffix for internal models
- LangGraph state keys: `snake_case` strings matching the TypedDict field name exactly

### TypeScript/JavaScript (services/worker, services/mcp-shopify, apps/web)
- Files: `kebab-case.ts` for utilities/lib, `PascalCase.tsx` for React components
- Variables/functions: `camelCase`
- Types/interfaces: `PascalCase`, prefix interfaces with `I` only when needed to disambiguate
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for true constants, `camelCase` for config objects
- Next.js routes: follow App Router conventions (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `route.ts`)

## Environment variables
- All env vars live in `.env.example` at the root (committed) and `.env.local` (not committed)
- Access via `os.getenv("VAR_NAME")` in Python with explicit fallback or raise on missing
- Access via `process.env.VAR_NAME` in Node; always validate at startup with zod schema
- Never hardcode API keys, model names, or service URLs ‚Äî always reference env vars
- Model name is always sourced from `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` env var (default: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`)

## Error handling
- All service boundaries (API endpoints, MCP tool calls, DB queries) must have try/except or try/catch
- Log the full error with context before re-raising or returning an error response
- Use structured logging everywhere ‚Äî JSON format in production, human-readable in dev
- Never swallow errors silently ‚Äî at minimum log them
- Python: use custom exception classes in `src/exceptions.py` per service
- TypeScript: use Result types or explicit error unions for domain errors; use thrown exceptions only for unexpected errors

## Logging
- Python: use `structlog` for structured JSON logging
- TypeScript: use `pino` for structured JSON logging
- Always include: `service`, `trace_id`, `entity_id` (when relevant), `signal_id` (when relevant)
- Log at INFO for normal operations, DEBUG for tool call details, ERROR for failures
- Never log raw API keys, personal data, or full SQL queries with values substituted

## Testing
- Python: pytest with async support (`pytest-asyncio`)
- TypeScript: Vitest for unit/integration, Playwright for e2e
- Every agent must have a test for: happy path, tool call failure recovery, guardrail rejection
- Mock all external APIs (Anthropic, Pipeboard, Shopify, ClickHouse) in tests
- Test files co-located: `tests/` directory at service root, mirroring `src/` structure

## Git conventions
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/`
- Commit style: conventional commits (`feat: add guardrail agent`, `fix: redis ttl overflow`)
- Never commit: `.env`, `*.pyc`, `__pycache__`, `node_modules`, `.DS_Store`

## Security rules (never violate)
- All Guardrail-classified QUEUE actions go to approval before any execution ‚Äî no exceptions
- Write MCP tools (budget change, campaign pause, product update) require `WRITE_ENABLED=true` env var to be set
- All approval queue items expire after 48 hours ‚Äî never auto-approve expired items
- ClickHouse queries must go through the query guard layer ‚Äî no raw user input in queries
- Never log full Claude API responses in production (may contain sensitive business data)
